--------------------/ ABSTRAKT: \--------------------
Educational platforms are being developed to provide highly personalized learning experiences. 
A key component of this personalization is recommendation systems that help to guide learners toward relevant resources. 
This paper seeks to investigate the technological, algorithmic, and pedagogical dimensions of recommendation systems in educational platforms, with a particular view toward one of the largest online learning platforms: Udemy. 
We go behind the scenes of Udemy's hybrid recommendation approach, enumerate the unique challenges of educational recommendations, and look at the system's impact on student engagement and completion rates. 
Lastly, we outline future developments in adaptive, AI-driven learning pathways and privacy-centered recommendation systems for education.
